title: Here We Go
body:
It's not having good time tonight
Give me a hell yeah
I said, give me a hell yeah (hell yeah)
Ladies, scream

Here we [C] go, here we [F] go
So alive, in the sky, we can [C] Fly
Here we [C] go, here we [F] go
So alive, in the sky, we can [C] Fly

Ladies and Gentlemen, I need a starlight
'Cause I never had a day without a fight
I slid through the darkness, it took me to a height
Of a lonesome, cold and never ending night

I'm the man on the moon, call me Andy Kaufman
There are demons inside me but I'm stomp'em
I know I can be an unstoppable force
I try, me, let me take a walk on the bright side

Here we [C] go, here we [F] go
So alive, in the sky, we can [C] Fly
Here we [C] go, here we [F] go
So alive, in the sky, we can [C] Fly

A lot of thoughts in my head keep pulling me down
So many guests in my house I could not notice the sound
Of the doorbell telling they're about to come
I'm surrounded by problems, I got to run

(But no) I keep pulling myself up
(But no) I keep pulling myself up
I'm on a mission to fulfill my vision
All day, everyday, never ever, ever give up

Here we [C] go, here we [F] go
So alive, in the sky, we can [C] Fly
Here we [C] go, here we [F] go
So alive, in the sky, we can [C] Fly
Here we [C] go, here we [F] go
Here we [C] go, here we [F] go
So alive, in the sky, we can [C] Fly

Scream big, scream loud
Scream big, scream loud
Scream big, scream loud Right now, right now
Scream big, scream loud
Scream big, scream loud
Scream big, scream loud Right now, right now
